1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
4
5 AS INTRODUCED
6 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,

Section 2:
Section 13-116, which relates to corporal punishment;
7 requiring school districts to report corporal
punishment administration annually; specifying report
8 requirements; requiring the State Department of
Education to compile and report corporal punishment
9 data; providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 13-116, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 13-116. A. School district personnel shall be
16 prohibited from using corporal punishment on students identified
17 with the most significant cognitive disabilities according to
18 criteria established by the State Department of Education unless
19 addressed in an annual individualized education program (IEP)
20 developed in accordance with the Individuals with Disabilities
21 Education Act (IDEA).
22 B. A waiver to the provisions of subsection A of this section
23 shall be granted if the parent or legal guardian of a student
24 provides written consent.
Req. No. 11707 Page 1
1 C. As used in this section, "corporal punishment" means the
2 deliberate infliction of physical pain by hitting, paddling,
3 spanking, slapping, or any other physical force used as a means of
4 discipline.
5 D. On an annual basis, each school district shall report to the
6 State Department of Education the following information:
7 1. The number of times corporal punishment was administered by
8 district personnel;
9 2. A record of the grade, age, race, gender, and disability
10 status of the student receiving corporal punishment; and
11 3. A record of the personnel administering the punishment, the
12 date and time of the incident, and the personnel who witnessed the
13 administration of corporal punishment.
14 E. On an annual basis, the State Department of Education shall
15 provide a compilation report on the administration of corporal
16 punishment to the Oklahoma Commission on Children and Youth.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
18 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
19 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
21 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
